Oswald ExtraLight Regular (Oswald-ExtraLight.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Oswald-ExtraLight', Everything looks good.

Pass

Oswald ExtraLight Regular (Oswald-ExtraLight.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Oswald' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraLight' = NID 1 'Oswald ExtraLight'.

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Oswald-Light', Everything looks good.

Oswald Light Regular (Oswald-Light.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Oswald' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light' = NID 1 'Oswald Light'.

Pass

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.

, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Oswald-Medium', Everything looks good.

Oswald Medium Regular (Oswald-Medium.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Oswald' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium' = NID 1 'Oswald Medium'.

Pass

Oswald SemiBold Regular (Oswald-SemiBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Oswald' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold' = NID 1 'Oswald SemiBold'.

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.

, most common Monotype license test is:
This font software is the property of Monotype Imaging Inc., or one of its affiliated entities (collectively, Monotype) and its use by you is covered under the terms of a license agreement. Font has no 'kern' table. Please verify if font requires kern table or if only GPOS kerning should be in font.

Info
